rComments: I took this class last summer. It was the best part of my summer to be honest. I loved going to lectures especially since I could just listen (no participation - my social anxiety thanks him a lot). He's a great lecturer, the midterm was very easy and he gave a list of possible exam questions so there's no way you could not pass this course.
Hard marker, he thinks he is an English professor. If you do attend class regularly and keep up with the readings and study for tests and exams you are guaranteed a B!

Course isn't hard (requires work) but the prof is a tough marker. His lecture style is all over the place/disorganized. Gives good clear outlines for tests. Course is largely based on 'primary source readings'. Thought I aced the exam, went in with a B+, came out with a C+. Wastes too much time on the artistic/musical part of European history.
